## Quickstart

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
pytest
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
```

`GET /healthz` returns 200 when the server is up.

The MCP server lives at `app/mcp/server.py` with explicit tool registration via `TOOL_REGISTRY`. Each tool currently returns a structured `ToolError` with `code=internal` and `message="Not yet implemented"` — implement the business logic in `app/domain/<tool>_logic.py` and the tool will start returning real data.

## Configuration

| Env var | Type | Default | Description |
|---------|------|---------|-------------|
| `SERVICE_NAME` | string | `<%= it.serverName %>` | Server identity in logs. |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | string | `INFO` | Log level. |
| `PORT` | int | `8000` | HTTP port for FastAPI. |

## Project layout

```
app/
  main.py            FastAPI app + lifespan
  api/               HTTP layer (health, errors, middleware)
  mcp/               Official mcp SDK server + TOOL_REGISTRY
    server.py
    tools/<name>.py  one file per tool (return ToolError stub)
  core/              config, logging, security seam, exceptions
  domain/            pure business logic (no FastAPI/mcp imports)
  services/          orchestration
  infrastructure/    external system clients
tests/
  unit/              per-tool tests
  integration/       /healthz + MCP server smoke
  contract/          input schema validation
  evals/             LLM-in-the-loop selection tests
```

## Security seam

`app/core/security.py` exports a stubbed `verify_internal_jwt()` that currently raises `NotImplementedError`. Wire your Okta/Entra/internal IdP here; the rest of the app already calls it via `Depends`.

